
[1]chrism

   CHRISM, n. Unguent; unction. In the Romish and Greek churches, oil
   consecrated by the bishop, and used in the administration of baptism,
   confirmation, ordination, and extreme unction. It is prepared on holy
   Thursday with much ceremony, and in some cases, mixed with balsam.
